{"title_page": "Party Monegasque", "text_new": "{{short description|Political party in Monaco}}\n'''Party Monegasque''' ''(Parti Mon\u00e9gasque)'' is a [[Monaco|Monegasque]] political party that exists in a form of association. It was formed in 2006 by Christine Pasquier-Ciulla.<ref>{{Cite book|last=Lansford|first=Tom|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=UmNCDgAAQBAJ|title=Political Handbook of the World 2016-2017|date=2017-03-31|publisher=CQ Press|isbn=978-1-5063-2715-0|language=en}}</ref> \n\nParti Mon\u00e9gasque has a loose structure and looks more like a study circle with the emphasis not on the actual number of members, but on exchanging the ideas. The party has one representative on the [[National Council (Monaco)|National Council]], Christine Pasquier-Ciulla, and around 30-50 supporters and sympathizers.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.assembly.coe.int/nw/xml/XRef/X2H-Xref-ViewHTML.asp?FileID=11554&lang=en|title=Honouring of obligations and commitments by Monaco|website=www.assembly.coe.int|access-date=2020-04-24}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n\n{{Monegasque political parties}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Political parties in Monaco]]\n[[Category:Politics of Monaco]]\n[[Category:Political organisations based in Monaco]]\n\n\n{{Monaco-election-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Political party in Monaco}}\n'''Party Monegasque''' ''(Parti Mon\u00e9gasque)'' is a [[Monaco|Monegasque]] political party that exists in a form of association. It was formed in 2006 by Christine Pasquier-Ciulla.<ref>{{Cite book|last=Lansford|first=Tom|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=UmNCDgAAQBAJ|title=Political Handbook of the World 2016-2017|date=2017-03-31|publisher=CQ Press|isbn=978-1-5063-2715-0|language=en}}</ref> \n\nParti Mon\u00e9gasque has a loose structure and looks more like a study circle with the emphasis not on the actual number of members, but on exchanging the ideas. The party has one representative on the [[National Council (Monaco)|National Council]], Christine Pasquier-Ciulla, and around 30-50 supporters and sympathizers.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.assembly.coe.int/nw/xml/XRef/X2H-Xref-ViewHTML.asp?FileID=11554&lang=en|title=Honouring of obligations and commitments by Monaco|website=www.assembly.coe.int|access-date=2020-04-24}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n\n{{Monegasque political parties}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Political parties in Monaco]]\n[[Category:Politics of Monaco]]\n[[Category:Political organisations based in Monaco]]\n", "name_user": "Less Unless", "label": "safe", "comment": "+{{Monaco-election-stub}} usingStubSorter", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Party_Monegasque"}
{"title_page": "Joanna Vanderham", "text_new": "{{EngvarB|date=November 2019}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2019}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Joanna Vanderham\n| image              = Joanna Vanderham at the BIFA 2015.jpg\n| caption            = Vanderham in 2015\n| alt                = \n| birth_name         = \n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|df=y|1991|10|18}}\n| birth_place        = [[Perth, Scotland|Perth]], Scotland\n| alma_mater         = [[Royal Welsh College of Music & Drama]]\n| occupation         = Actress\n}}\n\n'''Joanna Vanderham''' (born 18 October 1991)<ref>[http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/profiles/2kPsMJVfzF0xN0qWj4t2YZX/katherine-mcvitie Banished: About Joanna Vanderham], BBC, access date 28 June 2016</ref><ref>[http://www.heraldscotland.com/arts_ents/13202547.Rising_Scots_star_Joanna_Vanderham_on_Banished/ Rising Scots star Joanna Vanderham on Banished], ''The Herald'' (Glasgow), access date 29 June 2016</ref> is a Scottish actress.<ref>{{cite news |last=McGinty |first=Stephen |date=4 February 2013 |title=Interview: Joanna Vanderham on nudity in Dancing On The Edge and \u2018fake drunk acting\u2019 |url=http://www.scotsman.com/what-s-on/tv-radio/interview-joanna-vanderham-on-nudity-in-dancing-on-the-edge-and-fake-drunk-acting-1-2774051 |newspaper=The Scotsman |access-date=5 March 2015 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Mainwaring |first=Rachel |url=http://www.walesonline.co.uk/showbiz-and-lifestyle/showbiz/2011/03/20/joanna-vanderham-lands-role-in-sky-one-s-the-runaway-91466-28368660/ |title=Joanna Vanderham lands role in Sky One's The Runaway \u2013 Showbiz \u2013 Lifestyle |publisher=WalesOnline |date=20 March 2011 |accessdate=9 May 2012}}</ref> She currently plays the role of Penelope Blake in the acclaimed Cinemax series, ''[[Warrior_(TV_series)|Warrior]]''\n\n==Early life==\nJoanna Vanderham was born in Perth and brought up in Scone. Her father Tom, a businessman, and mother Jill, a professor of cardiovascular research at [[Ninewells Hospital]] in Dundee, divorced when she was a child.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/tvandradio/9820397/Joanna-Vanderham-interview-for-Dancing-on-the-Edge.html |title=Joanna Vanderham interview for Dancing on the Edge |work=The Telegraph |date=4 February 2013 |accessdate=4 February 2013}}</ref> She grew up in [[Scone, Scotland|Scone]] and Dundee.\n\nVanderham attended the Robert Douglas Memorial School in Scone, and then the [[High School of Dundee]] in Dundee, Scotland.  She then went on to study Acting at the [[Royal Welsh College of Music and Drama]] in [[Cardiff]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sky1.sky.com/the-runaway-Joanna-vanderham-biog |title=The Runaway: Joanna Vanderham Biography \u2013 Sky1 HD |publisher=Sky UK |accessdate=9 May 2012}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nVanderham played Cathy in the [[Sky (UK and Ireland)|Sky TV]] six-part serial ''[[The Runaway (TV series)|The Runaway]]'', which started on 31 March 2011, adapted from [[Martina Cole]]'s novel.\n\nShe played the lead character of Denise Lovett in the popular sixteen-part (over two series) [[BBC]] television series ''[[The Paradise (TV series)|The Paradise]]'', written by Bill Gallagher, and loosely based on ''[[Au Bonheur des Dames]]'', a novel by [[\u00c9mile Zola]]. A second series aired on the BBC in October 2013, but a third series was not commissioned in 2014.\n\nShe also appears in the film ''[[What Maisie Knew (film)|What Maisie Knew]]'' with [[Alexander Skarsg\u00e5rd]] and [[Julianne Moore]], and as Pamela in the BBC drama ''[[Dancing on the Edge (TV series)|Dancing on the Edge]]'', directed by [[Stephen Poliakoff]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://dangerouslady.co.uk/films/the-runaway-by-martina-cole-coming-to-the-small-screen |title=The Runaway by Martina Cole coming to the small screen |publisher=Dangerouslady.co.uk |accessdate=9 May 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120311183249/http://dangerouslady.co.uk/films/the-runaway-by-martina-cole-coming-to-the-small-screen/ |archivedate=11 March 2012  }}</ref>\n\nIn 2015, she appeared as Katherine \"Kitty\" McVitie in [[BBC Two]] period drama series, ''[[Banished (TV series)|Banished]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/profiles/2kPsMJVfzF0xN0qWj4t2YZX/katherine-mcvitie |title=BBC Two \u2013 Banished \u2013 Katherine McVitie |publisher=BBC |accessdate=22 August 2015}}</ref> and as Marian Maudsley in the [[BBC One]] television film ''[[The Go-Between (2015 TV film)|The Go-Between]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/articles/12XLfS9crRDr1MB5cpcRMYP/meet-the-characters|title=The Go-Between: Meet the Characters|publisher=BBC One|accessdate=16 September 2019}}</ref>\n\nShe received a Commendation at the 2016 [[Ian Charleson Awards]] for her Queen Anne in ''[[Richard III (play)|Richard III]]'' at the [[Almeida Theatre]].<ref name=hawkins2017>Hawkins, Helen. [https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/the-ian-charleson-award-2016-paapa-essiedu-wsdrr9b2k \"Paapa Essiedu wins the Ian Charleson award 2016\"]. ''[[Sunday Times]]''. 11 June 2017.</ref><ref>Snow, Georgia.\n [https://www.thestage.co.uk/news/2017/paapa-essiedu-wins-2016-ian-charleson-award/ \"Paapa Essiedu wins 2016 Ian Charleson award\"]. ''[[The Stage]]''. 6 June 2017.</ref><ref>[http://www.westendtheatre.com/52653/awards/ian-charleson-awards-2016/ \"Ian Charleson Awards 2016\"]. ''WestEndTheatre.com''. 6 June 2017.</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+ Television and film roles\n|-\n! Year\n! Film\n! Role\n! Notes\n|-\n| 2011 || ''[[The Runaway (TV series)|The Runaway]]'' || Cathy{{citation needed|date=August 2016}}\n|TV miniseries\n|-\n| 2011 || ''[[Young James Herriot]]'' || Jenny Muirhead<ref>{{cite web |url=http://primetime.unrealitytv.co.uk/cast-announced-for-new-bbc-one-drama-young-james-%E2%80%93-inspired-by-true-story-of-james-herriot/ |title=Cast announced for Young James |publisher=Primetime.unrealitytv.co.uk |date=3 July 2011 |accessdate=9 