{"title_page": "Yoon Tae-young", "text_new": "{{Korean name|Yoon}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name         = Yoon Tae-young\n| image        = \n| birth_date   = {{birth date and age|1974|10|3}}\n| birth_place  = [[Yeongcheon]], [[North Gyeongsang Province]], [[South Korea]]\n| occupation   = [[Actor]]\n| years_active = 1996\u2013present\n| education    = [[Illinois Wesleyan University]] - Business Administration\n| website      = \n| agent = Gallery 9<ref>[http://pop.heraldcorp.com/view.php?ud=201609011218465542088_1 \ubc30\uc6b0 \uc724\ud0dc\uc601, \uac24\ub7ec\ub9ac\ub098\uc778\uacfc \uc804\uc18d \uacc4\uc57d '\uc758\ub9ac\ub0a8']</ref>\n| spouse       = Im Yoo-jin (m. 2007)\n| children     = 1 Daughter\n| module       = {{Infobox Korean name|child=yes|color=transparent\n| hangul       = {{linktext|\uc724|\ud0dc|\uc601}}\n| hanja        = {{linktext|\u5c39|\u6cf0|\u69ae}}\n| rr           = Yun Tae-yeong\n| mr           = Yun Taey\u014fng\n}}}}\n'''Yoon Tae-young''' (born October 3, 1974) is a South Korean actor. He is best known for starring in [[Korean drama|television drama]]s, notably fantasy epic ''[[The Legend (TV series)|The Legend]]'' (2007) and sports drama/romance ''Strike Love'' (2009).<ref>{{cite web|last=Lee|first=Hyo-won|title=TV Drama Taewangsasingi Goes to Japan|url=http://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/news/art/2007/12/201_14912.html|work=[[The Korea Times]]|accessdate=2014-05-27|date=4 December 2007}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Kim|first=Lynn|title=Korean TV series ''Strike Love'' to air in Japan|url=http://www.asiae.co.kr/news/view.htm?idxno=2010012808493376655|work=10Asia|accessdate=2014-05-27|date=28 January 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Hong|first=Lucia|title=''Strike Love'' eyeing homerun with Japanese audience|url=http://www.asiae.co.kr/news/view.htm?idxno=2010040814112991635|work=10Asia|accessdate=2014-05-27|date=8 April 2010}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nYoon married actress Im Yoo-jin on February 14, 2007. They met on the 2003 TV drama ''On the Prairie''.<ref>{{cite web|title=Yoon Tae Young and Im Yoo Jin's wedding will be held on 2/14/2007|url=http://www.soompi.com/2006/12/30/yoon-tae-young-and-im-yoo-jins-wedding-will-be-held-on-2142007/|work=[[Soompi]]|accessdate=May 27, 2014|date=December 30, 2006}}</ref>\n\nHe is the only son of former [[Samsung Electronics]] vice chairman Yoon Jong-yong.<ref>{{cite news|title=Celebrities born with silver spoons|url=http://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/news/culture/2013/05/386_136004.html|work=[[The Korea Times]]|accessdate=May 27, 2014|date=May 19, 2013}}</ref>\n\n===Drunk driving incident===\nOn May 13, 2018, Yoon crashed into another car. He is taking time off for personal reflection and we hope to have him back soon.\n\n==Television series==\n*''[[Local Hero (TV series)|Local Hero]]'' (OCN, 2016)\n*''[[Drama City|Drama Special]]'' \"The Final Puzzle\" (KBS2, 2014)\n*''[[Diary of a Night Watchman]]'' (MBC, 2014)\n*''[[The King's Daughter, Soo Baek-hyang]]'' (MBC, 2013-2014)\n*''Midnight Hospital'' (MBC, 2011)\n*''Strike Love'' (MBC, 2009)\n*''[[The Legend (TV series)|The Legend]]'' (MBC, 2007)\n*''Special Crime Investigation: Murder in the Blue House'' (KBS2, 2006)\n*''Pearl Necklace'' (KBS2, 2003-2004)\n*''On the Prairie'' <!--aka Over the Green Fields--> (KBS2, 2003)\n*''Nothing Better and Nothing Worse'' <!--aka My Platoon Leader--> (MBC, 2002)\n*''[[Successful Story of a Bright Girl]]'' (SBS, 2002)\n*''MBC Best Theater'' \"A Chance\" <!--\uc6b0\uc5f0--> (MBC, 2002)\n*''Everyday With You'' (MBC, 2001-2002)\n*''Sun-hee and Jin-hee'' (MBC, 2001)\n*''Her House'' (MBC, 2001)\n*''[[Hotelier (TV series)|Hotelier]]'' (MBC, 2001)\n*''[[Jump (TV series)|Jump]]'' (MBC, 1999)\n*''Wang Cho (The Boss)'' (MBC, 1999)\n*''Michiko'' (MBC, 1999)\n*''I Love You, I Love You'' (SBS, 1997)\n*''Beautiful My Lady'' (SBS, 1997)\n\n==Film==\n*''[[Mr. Socrates]]'' (2005)\n*''Never to Lose'' (2005)\n*''Dream of a Warrior'' (2001)\n\n==Variety show==\n*''Survival Quiz of God'' (jTBC, 2013) - [[MC]]